	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Thomas</placeName>&#44; <date>24 January 1865</date></p>
				<p>To the Editor of the &#8220;Occident&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I had the pleasure to enclose an article<lb/> translated from the Curacaosche Courant of the <date>24th</date> Ulto&#44; which you will<lb/> oblige me to publish.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I would further request you to answer me the<lb/> following questions either by private letter or in the &#8220;Occident&#8221; as<lb/> they refer to a case happening at present in our Cong&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Which do you consider of greater importance &#8220;Confirmation or<lb/> Calling up to the Sefer&#63;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Can a Minister be justified in refusing to call up to the Sefer a lad<lb/> who has attained his religious Majority&#44; because he has not been<lb/> confirmed&#63;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">This Mr Editor is happening here&#44; a boy who completed his<lb/> 13th year since <date>April 64</date> has not yet been called up&#44; because he has<lb/> not been confirmed.  I blame the parents who blindly submit to such<lb/> arbitrary decision.&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am Mr Editor Your Most Obedt. Servt</p>
			<p rend="indent(3	)"><persName role="author">A Reformer</persName></p>
				<p>Enclosed please find my card.</p>
		</body>
